  "texts": [
    "This 29 There is an alternative parameterization that exists if Ĥf.v.",
    "Some works in the literature instead describe the decomposition as T = ĤBM and V = Ĥint, n.o. act..",
    "In the HF equations, V is then mean-field decoupled using δP = Pρ 0 instead of P, where P is the one-body density matrix in the active subspace.",
    "The resulting contributions to the HF Hamiltonian that are proportional to the reference state ρ 0 are equivalent to Ĥsub act.This perspective is implemented in the companion code.",
    "Correspondingly, the total energy is re-defined asE[P] = 1 2 Tr(T P) + 1 2 Tr (P -ρ 0)H HF [P -ρ 0],which is equivalent to the definition in the main text up to an unimportant overall constant.describes the 'restricted' HF variational manifold."
  ]
}